{"title": "Without a Hezbollah withdrawal from the border, Israeli troops may launch ground offensive", "tags": "world", "timestamp": "2024-09-29", "content": "LONDON \u2013 Israeli troops are continuing to mass at the country\u2019s borders with Lebanon amid growing fears that the killing of Hezbollah leader Hassan Nasrallah will soon be followed by an Israeli ground offensive against the radical militia, which operates from Lebanese soil.\nIsrael has already called up two brigades of reservists \u2013 around 4,000 soldiers \u2013 and has ordered their deployment to the country\u2019s northern border with Lebanon."}